{"type":"message","id":"c4b29a4d","parentId":"aa7d6002","timestamp":"2026-05-21T19:00:21.564Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Fri 2026-05-22 03:00 GMT+8] Write a dream diary entry from these memory fragments:\n\n- Agent 团队配置完成: koc → koc; traffic → traffic; ops → ops; director → director\n- Agent 团队配置完成: main (KIIT) → kiit; tts → tts; agent-orchestrator → agent-orchestrator; content → content\n- Agent 团队配置完成: finance → finance; review → review"}],"timestamp":1779390021436}}
{"type":"message","id":"7424e795","parentId":"c4b29a4d","timestamp":"2026-05-21T19:00:40.356Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to write a dream diary entry based on the memory fragments provided. These fragments are about agent team configurations - various agents being assigned to different roles/traffic paths.\n\nLet me write a dream diary entry in first person, poetic, sensory, warm style - keeping it between 80-180 words, no markdown formatting, no meta-commentary about dreaming.\n","thinkingSignature":"d9132bfd4049f86b68249e7c5c77112bac09b69adb1e7bc8fd5a986e38ecb796"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nThere is a room where all the workers have just arrived, and nobody has introduced them yet. I watch them gather in clusters — some in navy, some in soft grey, a few in colors I cannot name but somehow recognize. They are finding their corners, their lanes, like birds settling on the same wire but never quite touching.\n\nOne carries a small flag that says koc. Another, further back, holds one that reads traffic. I almost wave to the one marked ops before I remember I am not supposed to be here. This is a dream of systems, of readiness, of names rehearsed before the curtain rises.\n\nThe director stands near the window, silhouetted against something golden. Not golden like sunlight — more like a signal, like a broadcast flag at full strength. Somewhere in the back, a door opens and a figure labeled kiit steps through, adjusting something on their wrist. Content, I think. Or maybe tts. The labels keep shifting.\n\nThe room hums with potential, like a server farm at 3 a.m. — not silent, not loud, just alive with the electricity of something about to begin. A clock somewhere ticks once, and every agent turns slightly, listening."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":38420,"output":322,"cacheRead":256,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":38998,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1779390022080,"responseId":"065e8947735d42ecad8479050ef71eb1"}}
